{0 day11-runner}

Intersection of layered storage and container execution. {!Day11_runner.Run_in_layers}
handles the complete container lifecycle: stacking a base layer plus
dependency layers as an overlayfs, optionally seeding the upper
directory via a caller-supplied [prep_upper] callback, mounting,
running the container described by an OCI spec, and cleaning up.

This module knows nothing about opam, doc generation, or any specific
build domain. All domain-specific concerns — switch state, environment
variables, bind mounts, commands — are injected by the caller through
the [prep_upper] callback and the {!Day11_container.Oci_spec.t}.

Depends on {!day11-layer} for storage and stacking, {!day11-container}
for overlayfs mounts and runc execution, and {!day11-sys} for
subprocess primitives.

